In 2015 I graduated from college and moved home from Colorado with a degree in Mathematics, a lot of student loans, and a dream of attending grad school in Australia to study ocean engineering and sustainable energy. At the time, starting a handmade bikini company was a means to an end- a risky and probably illogical attempt to pursue this dream without falling into a â€œboring jobâ€ along the way. However, my accidental entrance into the fashion industry (the 2nd most polluting industry on the planet) exposed a devastating system of exploitation and greed. I quickly realized that if I wanted to make a difference in this world, Drift may be a really good place to start. My best friend agreed with me, so with her on board we expanded into making clothing as well- repairing and recreating disregarded 2nd hand clothes in the hopes of bringing new value to unwanted basics and forgotten vintage apparel. This posts marks the merging of our Instagrams, because we are busy creating more than just bikinis here at Drift and are excited to share it all with you, right here. Plus, less time spent on social media means more time to create ğŸ˜‰, so come check us out on Fleet Street.
